OL,3,CShip captain's claim of mechanical
OL,4,Cfailure before fatal crash ruled out
OL,6,FIn his defence, Motin, 59, said he
OL,7,Fmade a "mistake" and pressed the wrong
OL,8,Fbutton when he tried to take the
OL,9,FSolong out of autopilot and steer away
OL,10,Ffrom the Stena Immaculate from one
OL,11,Fnautical mile away.
OL,13,FNot realising the error, he told
OL,14,Fjurors that he proceeded to stop and
OL,15,Frestart the steering gear to no
OL,16,Feffect, thinking the Solong could have
OL,17,Fdeveloped a rudder fault experienced
OL,18,Fby sister ship, Sanskip Express.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/8
