OL,3,CShip captain's claim of mechanical
OL,4,Cfailure before fatal crash ruled out
OL,6,FShe told jurors it was "a button that
OL,7,Fhad he pressed, Mark Pernia would
OL,8,Fstill be alive, a simple task it is
OL,9,Finconceivable, using your clear logic
OL,10,Fand common sense, he would have been
OL,11,Funable to do".
OL,13,FShe said: "It would have been
OL,14,Fblindingly obvious to him that he had
OL,15,Fpressed the wrong button, and how to
OL,16,Frectify it if that is what happened.
OL,18,F"The reality is that he did nothing to
OL,19,Favoid collision. Instead he launched
OL,20,Finto a problem that had never occurred
OL,21,Fon the Solong.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/8
